The evidence with the title 'The Atlantic Community: november 2007 ' says Nov 29, 2007  ... Giuliani is " probably the most underqualified man since George Bush to seek the presidency, Rudy Giuliani - there's only three things he mentions in a sentence: a noun and a verb and 9/11." It's quite interesting right now to compare both the media coverage and debate formats in the US and Denmark. 
